### School of Universalism

#### Universal Savant
*2nd-level School of Transmutation feature*<br/>
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

The gold and time you must spend to copy a spell into your spellbook is halved.

#### Mastery of Fundamentals
*2nd-level School of Transmutation feature*<br/>
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You gain proficiency in the Arcana skill and your proficiency bonus is doubled for any ability check that uses it. If you already had proficiency in Arcana, you gain another proficiency of your choice from those offered by this class.

You know two additional number of cantrips of your choice from the wizard spell list, and an additional cantrip when you reach 6th, 10th, and 14th level in this class. These do not count against your number of cantrips known.

#### Improved Familiar
*6th-level School of Transmutation feature*<br/>
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You add the *find familiar* spell to your spellbook if you don't already have it. You can cast the spell using a 200 gp XXX instead of the normal material component. The XXX is not consumed unless the familiar is reduced to 0 hit points. 

When you summon a familiar this way, it gains the following benefits:
- You can cast a spell with a target of Self as though it had a target of Touch, targeting your familiar.
- Your familiar can communicate with others of its kind: cats with felines, hawks and owls and ravens with birds, lizards and snakes with reptiles, and so on.
- If the familiar is subjected to an effect that allows it to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, it instead takes no damage if it succeeds on the saving throw, and only half damage if it fails. It can't use this trait if it's incapacitated.
- When you or your familiar makes a Perception check while within arm's reach of each other, you may roll a d4 and add it to the total.

222
- You add your proficiency bonus to the familiar's AC.
- The familiar has an additional number of hit points equal to your wizard level.
- The familiar can attack using your spell attack bonus and spell save DC where appropriate. You can command it to do so as a bonus action.


